#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.42"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.42:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.42:0.2"
msgid "5. Cūḷavagga"
msgstr "5. The Lesser Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.42:0.3"
msgid "42. Tiṭhānasutta"
msgstr "42. Three Grounds"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.42:1.1"
msgid "“Tīhi, bhikkhave, ṭhānehi saddho pasanno veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"“There are three grounds, mendicants, by which a person with faith and "
"confidence can be known."

msgctxt "an3.42:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.42:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sīlavantānaṃ dassanakāmo hoti, saddhammaṃ sotukāmo hoti, "
"vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati muttacāgo payatapāṇi "
"vossaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato."
msgstr ""
"They like to see ethical people. They like to hear the true teaching. And "
"they live at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely generous, open-"
"handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to give and to share."

# Notice that the usual -ti is omitted here.
msgctxt "an3.42:1.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi ṭhānehi saddho pasanno veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"These are the three grounds by which a person with faith and confidence can "
"be known."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.42:2.1"
msgid "Dassanakāmo sīlavataṃ,"
msgstr "They like to see ethical people;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.42:2.2"
msgid "saddhammaṃ sotumicchati;"
msgstr "they want to hear the true teaching;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.42:2.3"
msgid "Vinaye maccheramalaṃ,"
msgstr "they’ve driven out the stain of stinginess:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.42:2.4"
msgid "sa ve saddhoti vuccatī”ti."
msgstr "that’s who’s called a person of faith.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.42:2.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
